cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the application of deep learning techniques for classification of hyperspectral data, which involves processing large volumes of data with high spectral resolution. This makes computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) the most likely categories. Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also relevant as the paper discusses the challenges of transferring models from multimedia images to hyperspectral data. Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) are also relevant as the paper focuses on deep learning approaches for classification.
